title: For Sale:  Colt Python 4" Bright Nickel 357 Magnum 1976
postcontent: This firearm is a fantastic example of what is arguably one of the finest revolvers that has ever been produced. These hand-built revolvers were first introduced in 1955 and produced until mid the 2000's, the now discontinued Colt Python is one of the most highly regarded revolvers in the world. Formerly manufactured by Colt's Manufacturing Company of Hartford, Connecticut. The Colt Python is sometimes referred to as a "Combat Magnum" or "Python Magnum".  Some firearm collectors and writers such as Jeff Cooper, Ian V. Hogg, Chuck Hawks, Leroy Thompson, Renee Smeets and Martin Dougherty have described the Python as the finest production revolver ever made.  This specific firearm was produced in 1976 and features a "Bright Nickel" finish and a 4" vent rib barrel with original wood handle. I have personally owned this firearm for over 20 years. I has sat in my gun safe for most all of that time. I bought it used but, it was like brand new when I bought it and since then I have only shot a box of shells through it. Firearm is still exceptionally clean with very light signs of carbon on cylinder face and very mild scoring on the cylinder gap. Gun is at a 96% condition. Action on this firearm is smooth, double and single action pull is perfect, crisp & tight. Bore is bright and very clean along with the rest of firearm. There are a few very light surface marks that have to be seen only under scrutinous inspection. Unfortunately, the original box and paperwork is NOT included with this firearm, as I never had it to begin with. Pictures are of exact firearm you will receive, Please feel free to contact via email if you have any questions or interest. Please leave a contact number and I will call you back as soon as I can. Thanks for looking!  Mark
